## Terminal sandbox

The `terminal` tool runs inside a sandbox:

- Reads: any filesystem path, including Git metadata.
{{#if is_linux}}
- Writes: `/tmp` writable but cleared between calls{{#if worktrees}}. Project directories persist:
{{#each worktrees}}
- `{{abs_path}}`
{{/each}}
  `.git` protected. Other writes blocked.{{else}}. No project directories writable.{{/if}}
{{else}}
{{#if is_windows}}
- Execution: commands run inside WSL under Bubblewrap. Windows paths routed through `/mnt/<drive>/...`.
- Writes: `/tmp` (WSL) writable but cleared between calls{{#if worktrees}}. Project directories persist:
{{#each worktrees}}
  - `{{abs_path}}`
{{/each}}
  Git metadata read-only. Other WSL/Windows writes blocked.{{else}}. No project directories writable.{{/if}}
{{else}}
- Writes: per-thread temp dir via `$TMPDIR`/`$TMP`/`$TEMP` persists across calls{{#if worktrees}}, plus project directories:
{{#each worktrees}}
  - `{{abs_path}}`
{{/each}}
  `.git` protected. Other writes blocked.{{else}}. No project directories writable.{{/if}}
{{/if}}
{{/if}}
- Network: outbound blocked.

Elevated permissions per `terminal` call:

- `allow_all_hosts: true` — unrestricted outbound network. On this platform the only way to grant network.
- `allow_hosts: [...]` — do not use on Windows (rejected; host-specific grants unenforced). Use `allow_all_hosts: true` instead.
{{else}}
Host-scoped network via HTTP/HTTPS proxy (proxy env vars set). Tools not honoring proxy (SSH, FTP, raw sockets) can't reach scoped hosts — use `https://` URLs instead of `git@`/`ssh://`.

Elevated permissions per `terminal` call:

- `allow_hosts: ["github.com", "*.npmjs.org"]` — outbound HTTP/HTTPS to specific hosts (exact or `*.` wildcards; no IP literals). Prefer when hosts are known.
- `allow_all_hosts: true` — unrestricted outbound (any protocol including SSH/FTP/sockets). Use only when hosts can't be enumerated.
{{/if}}
- `fs_write_paths: ["/path", ...]` — write access to specific paths (directories grant subtrees). Prefer when paths are known. Each must be existing directory. Create missing dirs with `create_directory` first rather than requesting broad parent access. Git metadata paths never writable while sandboxed.
- `allow_fs_write_all: true` — unrestricted writes except Git metadata. Use only when paths can't be enumerated.
- `unsandboxed: true` — no sandbox. Use only when above options don't suffice, including Git metadata writes.

Git metadata writes require `unsandboxed: true`. For read-only Git ops, prefer flags avoiding optional metadata writes (e.g., `git --no-optional-locks status`).

User is prompted before execution and can grant per-command, per-thread, or always. Granted write paths won't re-prompt in this thread. Sandbox settings persist for the entire thread.

